<item>
            <title>[SPARK-3759] SparkSubmitDriverBootstrapper should return exit code of driver process</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-3759</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;SparkSubmitDriverBootstrapper.scala currently always returns exit code 0. Instead, it should return the exit code of the driver process.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Suggested code change in SparkSubmitDriverBootstrapper, line 157: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;val returnCode = process.waitFor()
sys.exit(returnCode)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Workaround for this issue: &lt;br/&gt;
Instead of specifying &apos;driver.extra*&apos; properties in spark-defaults.conf, pass these properties to spark-submit directly. This will launch the driver program without the use of SparkSubmitDriverBootstrapper. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Linux, Windows, Scala/Java&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
